cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.DL 

The paper deals with predicting trends in online systems, which involves analyzing user behavior and interactions. This falls under the scope of social networks (cs.SOC) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of temporal bipartite networks and centrality measures also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and deep learning (cs.DL). Finally, the evaluation of prediction methods indicates a possible connection to computational social science (cs.SI).
